---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';

const updated = 'June 1, 2026';
const title = `Privacy Policy | ${SITE.name}`;
const description = `How ${SITE.name} handles your data: calculations run in your browser, your health inputs are never stored, and we keep tracking to a minimum.`;
---

<LegalLayout title={title} description={description} heading="Privacy Policy" updated={updated}>
  <div class="legal-note">
    <p>
      <strong>The short version:</strong> The numbers you type into our calculators
      stay on your device and are never sent to us. We don't require an account, and
      we keep any analytics minimal and consent-based.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how {SITE.name} ("we", "us", or "our") handles
    information when you visit our website and use our free health calculators and
    tools (the "Service"). By using the Service, you agree to the practices described
    here.
  </p>

  <h2>2. The data you enter into our tools</h2>
  <p>
    Our calculators (such as the BMI, calorie, and body-fat tools) run entirely in
    your web browser using client-side JavaScript. The values you enter — your
    height, weight, age, activity level, and similar inputs — are processed locally
    on your device to show your result.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>We do not transmit, collect, store, or share the health information you
    enter into our tools.</strong> When you close or reload the page, those values
    are gone unless your own browser chooses to autofill a form field.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Information we may collect automatically</h2>
  <p>
    Like most websites, our hosting and analytics providers may process limited
    technical information when you visit, such as:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Your approximate region (derived from your IP address)</li>
    <li>Browser type, device type, and operating system</li>
    <li>The pages you view and how you arrived at the site</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We use this aggregated, non-identifying information only to understand which
    tools are useful and to keep the site fast and reliable. Analytics cookies are
    only set if you consent — see our <a href="/cookie-policy">Cookie Policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Cookies and local storage</h2>
  <p>
    We use a small amount of local storage to remember your cookie-consent choice so
    we don't ask you on every visit. Non-essential cookies (for analytics) are loaded
    only after you accept them. You can change your choice at any time. Full details
    are in our <a href="/cookie-policy">Cookie Policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Third-party services</h2>
  <p>
    We rely on reputable providers for website hosting, content delivery, and
    optional, privacy-respecting analytics. These providers process technical data on
    our behalf and are not permitted to use it for their own purposes. We do not sell
    your personal information to anyone.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Children's privacy</h2>
  <p>
    The Service is intended for a general adult audience and is not directed to
    children under 13 (or the equivalent minimum age in your country). We do not
    knowingly collect personal information from children.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on where you live (for example, under the GDPR in the UK and EU, or the
    CCPA in California), you may have rights to access, correct, or delete personal
    information, and to object to certain processing. Because we don't collect the
    health data you enter and don't hold personal accounts, there is typically no
    personal profile for us to retrieve. If you have a request or question, please
    <a href="/contact">contact us</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Data security</h2>
  <p>
    We serve the site over encrypted HTTPS connections and follow industry-standard
    practices to protect the limited technical data our providers process. No method
    of transmission or storage is ever completely secure, but keeping calculations on
    your device greatly reduces risk by design.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we'll revise the
    "Last updated" date above. Significant changes will be highlighted on this page.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Contact us</h2>
  <p>
    If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please
    reach out through our <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
